					<outline text="Bearded drag queen wins Eurovision Song Contest | New York Post">
						<outline text="Link to Article" type="link" url="http://nypost.com/2014/05/10/bearded-drag-queen-wins-eurovision-song-contest/"/>
						<outline text="Archived Version" type="link" url="http://adam.curry.com/art/1399773704_yZP3Esft.html"/>
						<outline text="Sun, 11 May 2014 02:01"/>
						<outline text=""/>
						<outline text="COPENHAGEN, Denmark '-- Austrian bearded drag queen Conchita Wurst won the 59th edition of the Eurovision Song Contest Saturday with a James Bond-inspired power ballad."/>
						<outline text="The song, ''Rise Like a Phoenix,'' helped Wurst '-- the alter ego of 25-year-old Thomas Neuwirth '-- secure Austria's second victory in the competition. The country also won in 1966."/>
						<outline text="''This is dedicated to everyone who believes in a future of peace and freedom,'' a tearful Wurst said as she accepted the trophy from Denmark's Emmelie de Forrest, who won the contest last year. ''We are unity and we are unstoppable.''"/>
						<outline text="Pushing the boundaries of gender identity is nothing new at Europe's annual song contest '-- an extravaganza known for its eclectic, sometimes unlistenable lineup of techno beats, love songs and pop tunes. But Wurst had been faced with some protests before the competition, highlighting a rift between Europe's progressive liberal side and the traditional values and nationalist rhetoric of Russia and some other nations taking part."/>
