						<outline text="SCORES of female students kidnapped by Islamic militants from a north-eastern Nigerian school are free, Nigeria's military says."/>
						<outline text="Only eight of more than 100 students are unaccounted for, Major General Chris Olukolade said in a statement that gave no details."/>
						<outline text="''The others have been freed this evening,'' he said."/>
						<outline text="The government had reported that security forces were in hot pursuit of militants who abducted more than 100 females from a high school yesterday."/>
						<outline text="Borno state Governor Kashim Shettima told reporters that 129 students were kidnapped and at least 14 freed themselves: four of the students - aged between 16 and 18 - jumped off the back of a truck and 10 escaped into the bush when the extremists asked them to cook and were not paying attention."/>
						<outline text="''The others have been freed this evening,'' he said. http://www.theaustralian.com.au/news/world/islamists-free-kidnapped-nigerian-schoolgirls/story-e6frg6so-1226887579471"/>
