					<outline text="Ukraine eastern regions hold 'self-rule' vote today">
						<outline text="Link to Article" type="link" url="http://www.aljazeera.com/news/europe/2014/05/ukraine-eastern-regions-hold-self-rule-vote-20145114582932194.html"/>
						<outline text="Archived Version" type="link" url="http://adam.curry.com/art/1399815979_G3AZAdSq.html"/>
						<outline text="Source: bertb news feed" type="link" url="http://s3.amazonaws.com/radio2/bertb/linkblog.xml"/>
						<outline text="Sun, 11 May 2014 13:46"/>
						<outline text=""/>
						<outline text="Pro-Russian rebels have started to cast ballots in a &quot;self-rule&quot; vote in eastern Ukraine, a move criticised by the US as &quot;illegal&quot; and which could pull the former Soviet republic apart."/>
						<outline text="Sunday's poll, carried out as two &quot;referendums&quot; in the provinces of Donetsk and Lugansk, where armed men hold more than a dozen towns, marks a serious deepening of the political crisis in the country."/>
						<outline text="Although a &quot;yes&quot; vote would likely only be recognised by Russia, it would greatly undermine a presidential election which Ukraine is to hold in two weeks time, the AFP news agency reported."/>
						<outline text="The US and the European Union see the presidential election as crucial to restoring stability in Ukraine."/>
						<outline text="In a statement released on Saturday, Jen Psaki, the US State Department spokeswoman, said the referendums were &quot;illegal under Ukrainian law and are an attempt to create further division and disorder&quot;."/>
						<outline text="&quot;If these referenda go forward, they will violate international law and the territorial integrity of Ukraine. The United States will not recognise the results of these illegal referenda,&quot; she said."/>
						<outline text="In comments posted on Ukraine's presidential website on Saturday, acting president Oleksandr Turchynov said the vote would lead to &quot;a complete destruction of the economy, social programs and general life for the majority of the population&quot;."/>
						<outline text="&quot;This is a step into the abyss for the regions,&quot; Turchynov said."/>
						<outline text="Earlier on Saturday, France and Germany jointly threatened &quot;consequences&quot; on Russia if the presidential election is scuppered - echoing US President Barack Obama's warning of automatic sanctions that would slice into whole sectors of Russia's weakening economy."/>
						<outline text="Al Jazeera's Paul Brennan, reporting from Donetsk, said voters had been asked a &quot;deliberately coy&quot; question about self-rule."/>
						<outline text="He said &quot;it does not specify what form that rule may or may not take. It is deliberately coy&quot;."/>
						<outline text="Our correspondent also said the people in the east do not like the Kiev government but they do not necessarily want to break away."/>
						<outline text="A new poll by the Pew Global Attitudes Project shows a majority of those living in Ukraine - both in the restive east and more nationalist west - want the country's borders to remain intact, said our correspondent. "/>
						<outline text="The self-rule votes and presidential election come amid intensifying violence on the ground in east Ukraine."/>
						<outline text="Troops have been battling the well-armed rebels, who have barricaded themselves in towns and cities in Donetsk and Lugansk."/>
						<outline text="Despite rebel claims that the polling will reach 90 percent of the seven million people living in these two provinces, the areas they hold account for less than half that population."/>
						<outline text="Polling stations opened in schools in rebel-held territories at 8am (0500 GMT) and will close 12 hours later, according to rebel chiefs in the city of Donetsk."/>
						<outline text="Reporting from Kiev, Al Jazeera's Kim Vinnell said the Ukrainian government had dismissed the vote as &quot;illegitimate&quot;."/>
						<outline text="However, like in Crimea - which Russia annexed in March after a similar referendum - Ukraine has been powerless to stop preparations."/>
						<outline text="The government and its Western backers accuse Vladimir Putin, Russia's president, of deploying special forces in east Ukraine, as in Crimea, to see the vote through and to sabotage the May 25 presidential election."/>
						<outline text="Putin belatedly admitted sending military forces, but not special forces, to Crimea but continues to deny militarily meddling in east Ukraine."/>
						<outline text="554"/>
						</outline>
