						<outline text="Link to Article" type="link" url="http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-us-canada-27354269"/>
						<outline text="Archived Version" type="link" url="http://adam.curry.com/art/1399740243_fY62gffx.html"/>
						<outline text="Source: bertb news feed" type="link" url="http://s3.amazonaws.com/radio2/bertb/linkblog.xml"/>
						<outline text="Sat, 10 May 2014 16:44"/>
						<outline text=""/>
						<outline text="10 May 2014Last updated at 03:22 A drone almost collided with a US commercial flight in March, an official with America's flight regulatory agency has revealed."/>
						<outline text="Jim Williams of the Federal Aviation Administration's (FAA) unmanned aircraft systems office said it showed the risks posed by such aircraft."/>
						<outline text="The near collision was reported to air traffic control as a pilot approached a Florida airport."/>
						<outline text="The FAA currently only allows non-commercial and police uses for drones."/>
						<outline text="But it requires drone pilots to alert an airport when flying it within five miles (8km) of the airport."/>
						<outline text="'Catastrophic' results&quot;The airline pilot said that the UAS [unmanned aircraft system] was so close to his jet that he was sure he had collided with it,&quot; Mr Williams said at a drone conference in San Francisco."/>
						<outline text="&quot;Thankfully, inspection of the airliner after landing found no damage.&quot;"/>
						<outline text="American Airlines, which owns the aeroplane, said it was aware of the report and was investigating."/>
						<outline text="A FAA investigation was unable to identify the drone's owner or pilot, the agency said in a statement."/>
						<outline text="The use of drones has increased dramatically in the past few years as the aircraft have become cheaper and more accessible, putting the FAA under pressure to develop broader rules."/>
						<outline text="&quot;Our challenge is to integrate unmanned aircraft into the busiest, most complex airspace in the world,&quot; the agency said in a statement."/>
						<outline text="&quot;Introduction of unmanned aircraft into America's airspace must take place incrementally and with the interest of safety first.&quot;"/>
						<outline text="Mr Williams said on Thursday the &quot;risk for a small UAS to be ingested into a passenger airline engine is very real. The results could be catastrophic.&quot;"/>
						</outline>
